Comparison is real. It happens to even the best intentioned of us. But when we understand our unique voice, we can thrive in our specific gifting. Have you watched @alliworthington and @lisawhittle's teachings this month? If not, find some time to do that asap. We want to help you find your unique voice as a writer and speaker so you don't waste time comparing yourself to someone else.
.
Believe in the power of your own story. It will allow you to cheer for and support the story of someone else.
.
Sit for a minute and be captivated by where the Lord has brought you, and the impact and influence He wants you to have as you follow Him.
.
At #calledcreatives, we are writers and speakers captivated by purpose, teaming up, building and lifting each other in our callings. We love doing this with you! Tag someone whose story inspires you! ðŸ‘‡

Don't stress about your calling.

Soak those words in deep, today, friend.

God is the one who created you and gifted you, and He knows all you need before you even ask.

Ask Him for help. Do your due diligence. And then rest in your understanding that "He who has begun a good work in you will complete it... " (Phil.1:6)

Your calling is not something you are meant to muster up or fulfill by yourself. He will walk with you through the process.  #calledcreatives

Some of the fears that hold us back from writing: -"I'm not good enough."
-"I don't have enough time."
-"I'm intimidated by my favorite writer."
-"People will judge me for my story."
-"I don't want to hurt someone I love."
.
What is your fear/struggle that holds you back from writing? One of these? Or something else?
.
#CalledCreatives community is here to encourage each other. None of us are exempt from struggles/fear. Tell us what YOU'D love to write if all the worries, time issues, etc., went away. And tag someone you know who has a message inside of them, too. ðŸ‘‡
